			<p>In every business there is the one type of client that you should avoid at all costs. I estimate they represent about 10%-20% of all potential clients. They are the ones who expect the most, yet insist on paying the least and try to get as much as possible for free. These people also believe the know everything while in fact they know nothing. If you are for some reasons serving clients like that you are in trouble and you should change strategy for acquiring clients.</p>

