			<p>Most of these are not &#8216;horrible designer client habits&#8217; but instead simply realities of contracting.</p>
<p>Make no doubt about it &#8211; making your hourly pricing, overtime, printing costs, payment schedule, deliverable definition, resource delivery schedule, etc well defined in your contract is entirely *your* responsibility to think of and define with the client beforehand.</p>
<p>If you dont, its *your* bad habit as a contractor.</p>

		</li>

	
	
